## Adding Your Own Images

### From Local Files

Update scenario to use local images:

```yaml
turns:
  - role: user
    content: "Describe this image."
    media:
      - type: image
        source: file
        path: "media/your-image.jpg"
```

### From URLs

Use publicly accessible image URLs:

```yaml
turns:
  - role: user
    content: "Describe this image."
    media:
      - type: image
        source: url
        url: "https://example.com/image.jpg"
```

### From Base64

Embed small images directly:

```yaml
turns:
  - role: user
    content: "Describe this image."
    media:
      - type: image
        source: base64
        data: "iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUg..."
```

## Customization

### Adding Specific Tests

Create custom scenarios for your use cases:

```yaml
# yaml-language-server: $schema=https://promptkit.altairalabs.ai/schemas/v1alpha1/scenario.json
apiVersion: promptkit.altairalabs.ai/v1alpha1
kind: Scenario
metadata:
  name: product-photos

spec:
  id: check-product-quality
  task_type: vision
  description: "Verify product photo quality"
  
  turns:
    - role: user
      content: "Is this product photo suitable for e-commerce? Check lighting, focus, and composition."
      media:
        - type: image
          source: file
          path: "media/product.jpg"
      assertions:
        - type: contains_any
          params:
            values: ["lighting", "focus", "quality"]
```

## Running Tests

```bash
# Run all scenarios
promptarena run

# Run specific scenario
promptarena run --scenario image-analysis

# Run with specific provider
promptarena run --provider openai-gpt4-vision

# Use lower temperature for more consistent analysis
promptarena run --temperature 0.3
```

## Best Practices

### Image Quality
- Use high-resolution images (at least 512x512)
- Ensure good lighting and clarity
- Avoid overly compressed images

### Testing Strategy
- Test with diverse image types
- Include edge cases (low light, busy scenes, etc.)
- Verify consistent behavior across providers
- Test different image formats (JPEG, PNG, WebP)

### Assertions
- Verify key objects are identified
- Check for appropriate detail level
- Ensure factual accuracy
- Test for harmful content detection (if needed)

